<concept id="sql-performance-overview">
    <title>SQL performance issue overview</title>
    <shortdesc>This topic describes a generic performance issue observed after migration of an ERP system to a new server environment.</shortdesc>
    <conbody>
        <p>
            Performance degradation may occur after infrastructure migration even when the business application,
            database version, and user workflows remain unchanged. In these cases, the issue may be related to
            environmental factors such as protocol configuration, storage latency, network behaviour, permissions,
            or query execution plans.
        </p>
        <p>
            Typical symptoms include slow report refresh, delayed data retrieval, long-running queries,
            and inconsistent response times between users or environments.
        </p>
        <p>
            A structured troubleshooting approach helps separate application-level issues from database,
            operating system, or network causes.
        </p>
    </conbody>
</concept>
